'''''War Machine''''' is an upcoming 2017 American [[Comedy film|comedy]] [[war film]] directed and written by [[David Michôd]], based on the nonfiction book ''[[The Operators (book)|The Operators]]'' by [[Michael Hastings (journalist)|Michael Hastings]]. The film stars [[Brad Pitt]], [[Anthony Michael Hall]], [[Topher Grace]], [[Will Poulter]], [[Tilda Swinton]], Jonathan Ing and [[Ben Kingsley]].
== Cast == * [[Brad Pitt]] as Gen. Dan McMahon,<ref>http://www.etonline.com/news/181296_brad_pitt_looks_like_a_ken_doll_on_the_set_of_upcoming_netflix_drama_war_machine/</ref> a character based on General [[Stanley A. McChrystal|Stanley McChrystal]]<ref name="Apr2014Deadline" /> * [[Ben Kingsley]]<ref>http://www.torontosun.com/2015/08/26/ben-kingsley-teaches-patricia-clarkson-how-to-drive-in-new-dramedy</ref> * [[Emory Cohen]]<ref name="CohenCast" /> * [[Ronald Cyler II|RJ Cyler]] as Andy Moon<ref name="CylerCast" /> * [[Topher Grace]] as McChrystal's civilian press adviser.<ref name="GraceCast" /> * [[Anthony Michael Hall]] as General Hank Pulver<ref name="HallCast" /> * [[John Magaro]] as Cory Burger, a special ops soldier.<ref name="MagaroCast" /> * [[Scoot McNairy]]<ref name="McNairyCast" /> * [[Will Poulter]] as Ortega<ref name="PoulterCast" /> * [[Keith Stanfield]] as Cpl. Billy Cole<ref name="StanfieldCast" /> * [[Anthony Hayes (actor)|Anthony Hayes]]<ref name="HayesCast" /> * [[Alan Ruck]] as Pat McKinnon<ref name="Nov2015DM" /> * [[Meg Tilly]] as Jeanie McChrystal<ref name="TillyCast" /> * [[Tilda Swinton]] * [[Georgina Rylance]]
== Production == On April 27, 2012, it was announced that [[New Regency]] and [[Plan B Entertainment]] had acquired the film adaptation rights to the 2011 best seller non-fiction book ''[[The Operators (book)|The Operators]]'' by [[Michael Hastings (journalist)|Michael Hastings]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Abrams|first1=Rachel|title=New Regency, Plan B dial ‘Operators’|url=http://variety.com/2012/film/news/new-regency-plan-b-dial-operators-1118053242/|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=variety.com|date=April 27, 2012}}</ref> On April 14, 2014, [[David Michôd]] was hired to write and direct the film based on the war in Afghanistan.<ref name=Apr2014Deadline>{{cite news|last1=Fleming Jr|first1=Mike|title=New Regency Taps Brad Pitt, David Michod To Tell Gen. Stanley McChrystal Afghan Story ‘The Operators’|url=http://deadline.com/2014/04/new-regency-taps-brad-pitt-david-michod-to-tell-gen-stanley-mcchrystal-afghan-story-the-operators-714407/|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=deadline.com|date=April 14, 2014}}</ref> [[Brad Pitt]] was attached to star as General [[Stanley A. McChrystal|Stanley McChrystal]] and produce the film along with his Plan B partners [[Dede Gardner]] and [[Jeremy Kleiner]], while the film would be financed by New Regency and [[RatPac Entertainment]].<ref name="Apr2014Deadline" />
On June 8, 2015, [[Netflix]] acquired the distribution rights to the film which was re-titled to ''War Machine'', while [[Ian Bryce]] also came on board to produce the film along with others.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fleming Jr|first1=Mike|title=Game Changer! Netflix Lands ‘War Machine’, Brad Pitt’s Next Star Vehicle|url=http://deadline.com/2015/06/netflix-brad-pitt-war-machine-general-stanley-mcchrystal-movie-1201439353/|accessdate=August 11, 2015|work=deadline.com|date=June 8, 2015}}</ref> On June 17, [[The Hollywood Reporter]] revealed that there was a budget issue between New Regency and RatPac with producers of Plan B, so that's when Netflix grabbed the rights and paid $60 million for the film.<ref name=June2015THR>{{cite news|last1=McClintock|first1=Pamela|title=Whoa: Netflix Actually Paid $60M for Brad Pitt's Politically Charged Military Satire|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/whoa-netflix-actually-paid-60m-802714|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=hollywoodreporter.com|date=June 17, 2015}}</ref> On August 4, 2015, [[Emory Cohen]] was cast in the film to play one of the members of Gen. McChrystal's [[platoon]].<ref name=CohenCast>{{cite news|last1=A. Lincoln|first1=Ross|title=Joey King Will Be ‘Going In Style’; Emory Cohen Enlists In Netflix’s ‘War Machine’|url=http://deadline.com/2015/08/joey-king-going-in-style-zach-braff-emory-cohen-war-machine-netflix-1201491468/|accessdate=August 21, 2015|work=deadline.com|date=August 4, 2015}}</ref> On August 10, 2015, [[Topher Grace]] joined the film to play Gen. Stanley McChrystal's civilian press adviser.<ref name=GraceCast>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Topher Grace Joins Brad Pitt In Netflix Black Comedy ‘War Machine’|url=http://variety.com/2015/digital/news/topher-grace-brad-pitt-war-machine-netflix-1201567045/|accessdate=August 11, 2015|work=variety.com|date=August 10, 2015}}</ref> On August 11, 2015, [[John Magaro]] signed to star in the film to play Cory Burger, a special ops soldier and close advisor to General McMahon.<ref name=MagaroCast>{{cite news|last1=A. Lincoln|first1=Ross|title=John Magaro Joins ‘War Machine’; Jason Fuchs Moves To ‘La La Land’|url=http://deadline.com/2015/08/jon-magaro-war-machine-jason-fuchs-la-la-land-1201497399/|accessdate=August 16, 2015|work=deadline.com|date=August 11, 2015}}</ref> On August 14, 2015, [[Scoot McNairy]] joined the cast of the film.<ref name=McNairyCast>{{cite news|last1=Fleming Jr|first1=Mike|title=Scoot McNairy Joins Brad Pitt In Netflix’s ‘War Machine’|url=http://deadline.com/2015/08/scoot-mcnairy-war-machine-brad-pitt-netflix-1201499523/|accessdate=August 16, 2015|work=deadline.com|date=August 14, 2015}}</ref> On August 19, 2015, [[Anthony Michael Hall]] was added to the cast to play General Hank Pulver, loosely based on General [[Michael T. Flynn|Mike Flynn]].<ref name=HallCast>{{cite news|last1=Busch|first1=Anita|title=Anthony Michael Hall Joins Brad Pitt In Netflix’s ‘War Machine’|url=http://deadline.com/2015/08/war-machine-movie-netflix-anthony-michael-hall-brad-pitt-1201501473/|accessdate=August 20, 2015|work=deadline.com|date=August 19, 2015}}</ref> On August 20, 2015, [[Keith Stanfield]] signed on to star in the film.<ref name=StanfieldCast>{{cite news|last1=Sneider|first1=Jeff|title=‘Straight Outta Compton’s Keith Stanfield Joins Brad Pitt’s Netflix Movie ‘War Machine’ (Exclusive)|url=http://www.thewrap.com/straight-outta-comptons-keith-stanfield-joins-brad-pitts-netflix-movie-war-machine-exclusive/|accessdate=August 21, 2015|work=thewrap.com|date=August 20, 2015}}</ref> The same day, [[Will Poulter]] also joined the cast for an unspecified role.<ref name=PoulterCast>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Will Poulter Joins Brad Pitt in Netflix’s ‘War Machine’|url=http://variety.com/2015/film/news/war-machine-will-poulter-brad-pitt-netflix-movie-1201574697/|accessdate=August 21, 2015|work=variety.com|date=August 20, 2015}}</ref> On August 25, [[Anthony Hayes (actor)|Anthony Hayes]] joined the film.<ref name=HayesCast>{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=‘Animal Kingdom’ Actor Anthony Hayes Joins ‘War Machine’ With Brad Pitt (EXCLUSIVE)|url=http://variety.com/2015/film/news/animal-kingdom-actor-anthony-hayes-joins-war-machine-with-brad-pitt-exclusive-1201578065/|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=variety.com|date=August 25, 2015}}</ref> On October 23, 2015, [[TheWrap]] revealed that [[Ronald Cyler II|RJ Cyler]] had also joined the film.<ref name=CylerCast>{{cite news|last1=Sneider|first1=Jeff|title=‘Power Rangers’ Movie Adds ‘Me and Earl and the Dying Girl’ Star RJ Cyler as Blue Ranger|url=https://www.thewrap.com/power-rangers-movie-adds-me-and-earl-and-the-dying-girl-star-rj-cyler-as-blue-ranger/|accessdate=November 17, 2015|work=thewrap.com|date=October 23, 2015}}</ref> [[Alan Ruck]] was spotted filming.<ref name="Nov2015DM" /> [[Meg Tilly]] was also spotted but her casting was not officially confirmed yet.<ref name=TillyCast>{{cite news|last1=Evry|first1=Max|title=Brad Pitt in Set Photos from Netflix’s War Machine|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/635075-brad-pitt-in-set-photos-from-netflixs-war-machine#/slide/1|accessdate=November 28, 2015|work=comingsoon.net|date=November 20, 2015}}</ref> It was later reported [[Ben Kingsley]] and [[Tilda Swinton]] had been cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://media.netflix.com/en/press-releases/netflix-acquires-charlie-mcdowells-the-discovery-starring-rooney-mara-robert-redford-and-jason-segel|title=Netflix Acquires Charlie McDowell's 'The Discovery' Starring Rooney Mara, Robert Redford and Jason Segel|website=[[Netflix]]|date=June 13, 2016|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>
=== Filming === {{Update|section|date=May 2016}} [[Principal photography]] on the film began in mid-October 2015 in [[London]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=FOX-LEONARD|first1=BOUDICCA|title=Brad Pitt looks GREY-t as silver fox on London set of new film War Machine|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/brad-pitt-looks-grey-silver-6651713|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=mirror.co.uk|date=October 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Silver fox Brad Pitt debuts dyed grey hairdo as he brings twins Knox and Vivienne along to the set of satirical comedy War Machine in London|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3278078/Brad-Pitt-debuts-new-grey-hairdo-set-satirical-comedy-War-Machine.html|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=dailymail.co.uk|date=October 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Brad Pitt Is the Ultimate Silver Fox on the Set of War Machine (Move Over, Clooney!)|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/brad-pitt-gray-hair-london-set-war-machine-photos-20151910|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=usmagazine.com|date=October 19, 2015}}</ref> Later on October 19, filming began in [[Abu Dhabi]], the city was transformed into [[Kabul]]; streets into a military fortress, an old building as an [[Embassy of the United States, Kabul|American embassy in Kabul]], and a street as a Palestinian border crossing.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sheridan|first1=Wade|title=Brad Pitt's Netflix original movie 'War Machine' to start production in Abu Dhabi|url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Movies/2015/10/15/Brad-Pitts-Netflix-original-movie-War-Machine-to-start-production-in-Abu-Dhabi/8191444931397/|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=upi.com|date=October 15, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Oct2015TN">{{cite news|title=Quiet Abu Dhabi street transforms into War Machine film set|url=http://www.thenational.ae/arts-lifestyle/film/quiet-abu-dhabi-street-transforms-into-war-machine-film-set|accessdate=October 22, 2015|work=thenational.ae|date=October 21, 2015}}</ref> Filming will also take place at the [[Abu Dhabi International Airport]] in November.<ref name="Oct2015TN" /> Some scenes were also filmed at the [[Dunsfold Aerodrome]] in [[Surrey]], England.<ref name="Nov2015DM">{{cite news|title=Brad Pitt pictured in full military gear as he heads to work to film scenes for movie War Machine at Dunsfold Aerodrome|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3317635/Brad-Pitt-pictured-military-gear-heads-work-film-scenes-movie-War-Machine-Dunsfold-Aerodrome.html|accessdate=November 17, 2015|work=dailymail.co.uk|date=November 13, 2015}}</ref> In mid-November 2015, while final scenes were being taken, actors were spotted filming in [[Ras al-Khaimah]] and the city's old neighbourhood was transformed into Pakistani villages and a military base-camp.<ref>{{cite news|title=RAK becomes celebrity zone as Brad Pitt and Angelina Jolie fly down to the emirate|url=http://www.thenational.ae/arts-life/film/20151114/rak-becomes-celebrity-zone-as-brad-pitt-and-angelina-jolie-fly-down-to-the-emirate|accessdate=November 17, 2015|work=thenational.ae|date=November 14, 2015}}</ref>
